TRUSTABLE-SOFTWARE: This
release of JSON-Library
also reffered in the
documentation as nlohmann/json
library is Trustable.

TT-EXPECTATIONS: Documentation
is provided, specifying
what nlohmann/json library
is expected to do, and
what it must not do,
and how this is verified.
AOU-22: Numbers are written\nin base 10.

JLEX-02: The requirement\nregarding [JSON Deserialization](https://eclipse-score.github.io/score/main/modules/baselibs/json/docs/requirements/index.html#comp_req__json__deserialization)\nis fulfilled.

PJD-03: The service parses
all texts that conform
to the JSON grammar.
NPF-02: The service parses\nnumbers according to\nRFC8259.

NPF-02.1: The service
parses integers without
exponent within the precision
of int64_t.

NPF-02.10: The service
ignores trailing zeroes
after the decimal point.

NPF-02.11: The service
parses numbers within
the 64-bit double range
but outside of the double
precision without throwing
an exception.
NPF-02.12: The service\nignores capitalisation\nof the exponent.

NPF-02.2: The service
parses integers with
exponent within the precision
of 64-bit double.

NPF-02.3: The service
parses floating point
values without exponent
within the precision
of 64-bit double.

NPF-02.4: The service
parses floating point
values with exponent
within the precision
of 64-bit double.
NPF-02.5: The service\nignores leading zeroes\nin the exponent.

NPF-02.6: The service
parses integers within
IEEE 754-2008 binary64.
NPF-02.7: The service\nignores leading and trailing\nwhitespace.

NPF-02.8: The service
ignores one singular
leading plus of the exponent.

NPF-02.9: The service
parses floating point
numbers within IEEE 754-2008
binary64 standard.

PJD-04: The service correctly
parses 64-bit integers
(exceeding the range
defined in RFC8259).

TA-BEHAVIOURS: Expected
or required behaviours
for nlohmann/json library
are identified, specified,
verified and validated
based on analysis.
